A shooting incident, believed to be taxi-related, has taken place on the N11 in northern Natal this morning (October 31). Police are treating the incident as a high priority crime, with at least 10 people dead, three critically injured and others wounded. It is believed that some of the dead are children. Early reports say that a taxi transporting children came under fire. Emergency services are en-route. The Ladysmith Gazette will be updating the story. Read original story on ladysmithgazette.co.za